  <section>
    <h2>Preventive Care That Catches Problems Early</h2>
    <p>
      Your pet can't tell you when something feels off — but a thorough wellness exam can uncover issues long before they become serious. At Healthy Paws Animal Hospital in Lake in the Hills, IL, we believe preventive care is the single best thing you can do to give your dog or cat a longer, healthier life. Our comprehensive wellness exams go far beyond a quick once-over, giving you a complete picture of your pet's health at every stage.
    </p>
    <p>
      As a practice <strong>dedicated to gentle, low-stress care</strong>, we've designed every part of the visit — from the waiting room to the exam table — to reduce stress and anxiety for your pet. That means calmer patients, more accurate exams, and a better experience for everyone.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What Happens During a Wellness Exam</h2>
    <p>
      Every wellness visit at Healthy Paws includes a detailed <strong>nose-to-tail physical examination</strong>. Our veterinarians take the time to evaluate each body system so nothing gets missed:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Eyes, ears, and nose</strong> — checked for discharge, infection, inflammation, and abnormalities</li>
      <li><strong>Dental assessment</strong> — teeth, gums, and oral health evaluated for tartar buildup, gingivitis, or fractured teeth</li>
      <li><strong>Heart and lungs</strong> — listened to with a stethoscope to detect murmurs, arrhythmias, or respiratory concerns</li>
      <li><strong>Abdominal palpation</strong> — gentle examination of internal organs to check for masses, pain, or organ enlargement</li>
      <li><strong>Skin and coat</strong> — inspected for lumps, rashes, parasites, hair loss, and overall condition</li>
      <li><strong>Joint and mobility assessment</strong> — range of motion and gait evaluated, especially important for large breeds and senior pets</li>
      <li><strong>Weight check and body condition scoring</strong> — tracked over time to identify trends early</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Beyond the physical exam, we'll review your pet's <a href="/pet-vaccinations-lake-in-the-hills-il/">vaccination status</a>, discuss parasite prevention, assess nutrition, and talk through any behavioral changes you've noticed at home.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Wellness Exams by Life Stage</h2>

    <h3>Puppies and Kittens (Under 1 Year)</h3>
    <p>
      Those first months are critical. Puppies and kittens need a series of visits — typically every 3 to 4 weeks — for vaccines, deworming, and developmental checkups. We'll make sure your new family member is growing on track, discuss spay/neuter timing, and answer all of your new-pet questions. Our <a href="/low-stress-vet-lake-in-the-hills-il/">gentle, low-stress approach</a> helps young pets build positive associations with the veterinary clinic from day one.
    </p>

    <h3>Adult Dogs and Cats (1–6 Years)</h3>
    <p>
      Healthy adult pets should visit us at least once a year. Annual exams help us catch subtle changes — a few extra pounds, early dental disease, a new lump — before they snowball into bigger problems. We'll update vaccines, refill preventive medications, and adjust our recommendations based on your pet's lifestyle.
    </p>

    <h3>Senior Pets (7+ Years)</h3>
    <p>
      Older pets age faster than we realize. A lot can change in six months, which is why we recommend <strong>semi-annual wellness exams</strong> for senior dogs and cats. These visits include more comprehensive <a href="/laboratory-diagnostics/">bloodwork and diagnostics</a> to screen for age-related conditions like kidney disease, diabetes, thyroid disorders, and arthritis. Our <a href="/senior-pet-care-lake-in-the-hills-il/">senior pet care program</a> is built to help your companion stay comfortable and active in their golden years.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Bloodwork and Diagnostic Screening</h2>
    <p>
      A physical exam tells us a lot — but it can't show us everything. That's why we recommend baseline and routine bloodwork as part of your pet's wellness plan. Diagnostics we may recommend include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Complete blood count (CBC)</strong> — evaluates red and white blood cells and platelets</li>
      <li><strong>Chemistry panel</strong> — assesses kidney function, liver enzymes, blood glucose, and electrolytes</li>
      <li><strong>Thyroid screening</strong> — especially important for senior cats and dogs</li>
      <li><strong>Urinalysis</strong> — checks kidney concentration, infection, and crystals</li>
      <li><strong>Heartworm and tick-borne disease testing</strong> — annual screening recommended for all dogs</li>
      <li><strong>Fecal parasite testing</strong> — screens for intestinal worms and other parasites</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Running these tests when your pet is healthy gives us a baseline. When values change down the road, we'll know what's normal for <em>your</em> pet — not just the average.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Nutrition and Lifestyle Review</h2>
    <p>
      Every wellness exam includes a conversation about what your pet eats, how much they exercise, and any changes in behavior or habits. Weight management is one of the most impactful things we can address — over half of pets in the U.S. are overweight, and extra pounds contribute to joint problems, diabetes, and a shorter lifespan. Our team provides personalized <a href="/nutrition-counseling/">nutrition counseling</a> to keep your pet at an ideal weight.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>A Stress-Free Experience for Your Pet</h2>
    <p>
      Wellness visits shouldn't be something you or your pet dread. Our team is trained in <strong>gentle, low-stress handling techniques</strong> — that means gentle restraint, calming pheromones, treats and positive reinforcement, and a pace that works for your pet. We want every visit to be as low-stress as possible, so your pet is happy to come back.
    </p>
    <p>
      Cats get special attention, too. If you have a feline family member, learn more about our <a href="/cat-vet-lake-in-the-hills-il/">cat-friendly veterinary care</a> designed specifically for their unique needs.
    </p>
  </section>

